&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for a change in your nursing role this Winter? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for committed and enthusiastic Registered Nurses to join our supportive community nursing inpatient ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Leonard’s Ward at Wallingford Community Hospital is looking for you to join their friendly, highly motivated and caring team. You should have an interest in rehabilitation and recovery, with a good knowledge, excellent communication skills and a flexible positive attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of our nurse-led multidisciplinary team providing a high level of nursing care to our patients who are part of the local community, to help them be able to return home again following hospital admittance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can provide a comprehensive induction and training programme whilst working in a wonderful supportive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wallingford Community Hospital is located just down the road from the lovely town of Wallingford in South Oxfordshire with easy access to Oxford, Henley and Reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible requirement to work a variety of shift patterns is essentials. Our shift patterns are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Early Shift 07:30-15:30&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Late Shift 13:00-21:00&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Night Shift 20:45-07:45&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;An informal phone conversation is strongly encouraged during the application stage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Andy Armsby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
